.TH "skb_checksum_maybe_trim" 9 "skb_checksum_maybe_trim" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
skb_checksum_maybe_trim \- maybe trims the given skb
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sk_buff *" skb_checksum_maybe_trim
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "unsigned int transport_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
the skb to check
.IP "transport_len" 12
the data length beyond the network header
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether the given skb has data beyond the given transport length.
If so, returns a cloned skb trimmed to this transport length.
Otherwise returns the provided skb. Returns NULL in error cases
(e.g. transport_len exceeds skb length or out-of-memory).

Caller needs to set the skb transport header and free any returned skb if it
differs from the provided skb.
